# 📊 Blueprint: Unified Data Visualization & Storytelling Lab

This guide maps how to spin up a centralized visualization hub, ingest data from both your analytical sandbox and home automation suite, and design query loops that tell an actionable data story.

```
 [ MarTech Database ]             [ Home Assistant ]
   (PostgreSQL Core)                      | (InfluxDB Integration)
           |                              v
           |                      [ InfluxDB TSDB ]
           |                       (Time-Series DB)
           v                              |
 [ Apache Superset ] <--------------------+--------------------> [ Grafana Engine ]
(MarTech Funnel Analytics)                                   (IoT Time-Series Matrix)

```

## 🐋 1. The Visualization Infrastructure (`docker-compose.yml`)

Add these blocks right into your existing `martech-sandbox` or a new `viz-sandbox` directory on your Dell R710 virtual host. This spins up Apache Superset, Grafana, and an InfluxDB time-series database.

```yaml
version: '3.8'

services:
  # Tier 1: Open-Source Business Intelligence & Storytelling Engine (Looker Studio Alt)
  superset:
    image: apache/superset:latest
    container_name: superset_bi
    ports:
      - "8088:8088"
    environment:
      - SUPERSET_SECRET_KEY=change_this_to_a_long_random_string_key_1234
      - TALISMAN_CONFIG={"force_https":False}
    volumes:
      - superset_home:/app/superset_home
    command: >
      sh -c "superset db upgrade &&
             superset fab create-admin --username admin --firstname Analytics --lastname Admin --email admin@lab.io --password superset_secret_pass &&
             superset init &&
             superset run -p 8088 -h 0.0.0.0 --with-threads"
    restart: unless-stopped

  # Tier 2: Time-Series Database for Home Assistant Telemetry
  influxdb:
    image: influxdb:1.8-alpine
    container_name: home_telemetry_db
    ports:
      - "8086:8086"
    environment:
      - INFLUXDB_DB=homeassistant
      - INFLUXDB_ADMIN_USER=db_admin
      - INFLUXDB_ADMIN_PASSWORD=influx_secret_pass
    volumes:
      - influxdb_data:/var/lib/influxdb
    restart: unless-stopped

  # Tier 3: Core Infrastructure Dashboard Engine
  grafana:
    image: grafana/grafana:latest
    container_name: grafana_viz
    ports:
      - "3000:3000"
    volumes:
      - grafana_storage:/var/lib/grafana
    restart: unless-stopped

volumes:
  superset_home:
  influxdb_data:
  grafana_storage:

```

Launch the stack:

```bash
docker compose up -d

```

